<div class="deleted-pen-content">
<% if deleted_pens.count == 0 %>
  <div class="no-deleted-pen">
    <h2>You don't have any deleted Pens.</h2>
    <blockquote style="max-width: 25em; margin: 2rem auto;">
      If you want to save our world, you must hurry. We don't know how much longer we can withstand the nothing.<br><br><cite>— Southern Oracle, The Neverending Story</cite>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
<% else %>
  <div class="deleted-pen-item">
    <% deleted_pens.each do |pen| %>
    <div class="deleted-pen-wrap" data-controller="delete-pen"
                                  data-delete-pen-random-value="<%= pen.random_url %>"
                                  data-delete-pen-username-value="<%= current_user.username %>"
                                  data-delete-pen-target="trashedPen">
      <h2 data-delete-pen-target="trashedPenTitle">
        <%= pen.title %>
      </h2>
      <div class="deleted-pen-button">
        <span class="hidden" data-delete-pen-target="restoreNotice">
          Restoring...
        </span>
        <span class="hidden" data-delete-pen-target="deleteNotice">
          Deleting...
        </span>
        <button data-delete-pen-target="restoreBtn"
                data-action="click->delete-pen#restore">
          Restore
        </button>
        <button data-delete-pen-target="reallyDeleteBtn"
                data-action="click->delete-pen#trashPopup">
          Really Delete
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
<% end %>
  <div class="deleted-pen-notice">
    <div>
      <h3>🕖 1 hour</h3>
      <p>You’ll be able to restore a Pen for 1 hour after you delete it. After that, it’s gone forever.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>✍️ Just the Code</h3>
      <p>When you restore a Pen, it's just the code and all settings. You don't get the hearts, view count, or comments.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

